verbose_text: Lower baseline pH level was positively related with change in gray matter volume by day 5 (sr 2 = 7.51%, P = 0.006); negatively associated with baseline white matter diffusivity in the frontal (sr 2 = 41.3%, P < 0.001), temporal (sr 2 = 33.03%, P < 0.001), and parietal (sr 2 = 24.07%, P < 0.001) regions; but positively associated with 6-month frontal gray matter diffusivity (sr 2 = 11.9%, P = 0.008).
